{"word":"ῥαψῳδός","slug":"ῥαψῳδός","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<entryFree id=\"n92252\" key=\"r(ayw|do/s\" type=\"main\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"entryFree\"> <orth extent=\"suff\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"orth\">ῥαψῳδ-ός</orth>, <gen lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gen\">ὁ</gen>, <sense id=\"n92252.0\" n=\"A\" level=\"1\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"sense\"> <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">reciter of Epic poems</tr_>, sts. applied to the <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">bard who recited his own poem</tr_>, as to Hesiod, <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\">Nicocl.</author> </bibl> ap. Sch.<bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0033.tlg003.perseus-grc1:2:2\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Pi.\">Pi.</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\">N.</title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">2.2</biblScope> </bibl> (v. infr.); but usu., <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">professional reciters</tr_>, esp. <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">of the poems of Homer</tr_>, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0016.tlg001.perseus-grc1:5:67\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Hdt.\">Hdt.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">5.67</biblScope></bibl>, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0059.tlg027:530c\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Pl.\">Pl.</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Ion\">Ion</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">530c</biblScope></bibl>, etc.: also <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ῥ. κύων</foreign>, ironically, of the Sphinx who <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">chanted</tr_> her riddle, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0011.tlg004.perseus-grc1:391\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ S.\">S.</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ OT\">OT</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">391</biblScope></bibl>. (Prob. from <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ῥάπτω, ἀοιδή</foreign>; <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0020.tlg007:265\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Hes.\">Hes.</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Fr.\">Fr.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">265</biblScope> </bibl> speaks of himself and Homer as <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ἐν νεαροῖς ὕμνοις ῥάψαντες ἀοιδήν</foreign>, and <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0033.tlg003.perseus-grc1:2:2\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Pi.\">Pi.</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\">N.</title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">2.2</biblScope> </bibl> calls Epic poets <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ῥαπτῶν ἐπέων ἀοιδοί</foreign>: not from <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ῥάβδος</foreign> (cf. <cit TEIform=\"cit\"> <quote_ lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"quote\">ῥάβδος</quote_> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0033.tlg003.perseus-grc1:1:6\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">1.6</biblScope> </bibl> </cit>) as if <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ῥαβδῳδός</foreign> (<bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg4083.tlg001:6:24\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Eust.\">Eust.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">6.24</biblScope></bibl>, <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ῥαβδῳδία</foreign> ib.<bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg4083.tlg001:16\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">16</biblScope> </bibl>).)</sense> </entryFree>"}]}